Case 20-2413. Document 107. 09/11/2020. 2929023, Pagel of 2 
S.D.N.Y. 
20-2413 
Loretta A. Preska, 3. 
United States 
Court of Appeals 
FOR THE 
SECOND 
CIRCUIT 
At a stated term of the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit, held at the 
Thurgood Marshall United States Courthouse, 40 Foley Square, in the City of New York, on the 
11th day of September, two thousand twenty. 
Plaintiff:Appellee, ORDER 
v. 20-2413 
Ghislaine Maxwell, 
Defendant-Appellant. 
Sharon Churcher, Jeffrey Epstein, 
Respondents, 
Julie Brown, Miami Herald Media Company, Alan M. 
Dershowitz, Michael Cemovich, DBA Cemovich Media, 
Intervenors. 
It is hereby ORDERED that the United States shall submit an amicus letter brief, not to 
exceed ten (10) double-spaced pages, regarding (I) arguments raised by Defendant-Appellant 
Ghislaine Maxwell and (2) Defendant-Appellant Ghislaine Maxwell's motion to consolidate this 
appeal with United States v. Maxwell, No. 20-3061. The United States shall submit its brief no 
later than Wednesday, September 16, 2020 at 3:00 pm. 
It is also hereby ORDERED that the parties to the appeal shall respond to the letter brief 
filed by the United States by Wednesday, September 23, 2020 at 3:00 pm. 
EFTA00028060

Case 20-2413. Document 107. 09/11:2020. 2929023, Page2 of 2 
The hearing scheduled for Tuesday, September 22, 2020 at 2:00 pm is hereby 
ADJOURNED until further order of the court. 
For the 
Court: 
Catherine O'Hagan Wolfe, 
Clerk of 
Court 
EFTA00028061
